  "html": "<article class=\"max-w-4xl mx-auto\">\n\n  \n  <section class=\"gradient-flame-sunglow text-white p-5 md:p-10 rounded-2xl mb-8\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold mb-4 text-white\">Your Family Needs Power. You Need Answers.</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed opacity-95\">\n      Here's the thing nobody tells you when you start researching solar for Cuba: the \"best\" panel means nothing if your tío can't install it, it gets fried by humidity in six months, or customs holds it for three weeks. I've watched too many well-meaning diaspora folks drop serious money on systems that ended up as expensive roof decorations. Let's fix that.\n    </p>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none mb-10\">\n    <p>\n      The blackouts aren't getting better. You know it, I know it, and your family calling at 2 AM definitely knows it. So you're here trying to figure out whether to send a complete solar kit with panels, charge controllers, and all the wiring—or just grab a power station that plugs in and stores juice. Both work. Both have serious trade-offs for Cuba specifically.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      <strong>Solar panel kits</strong> are the long game: more complex to install, but they generate their own power indefinitely. <strong>Power stations</strong> are grab-and-go—charge them when there's grid power, use them during apagones—but they're only as good as their battery capacity and how often the grid actually comes back.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      What matters for Cuba? Voltage flexibility (110V is standard there, but some areas have 220V), humidity resistance (that salitre will eat cheap electronics alive), shipping weight and dimensions, and whether someone in the family actually knows how to wire things. Let's break this down by what your family actually needs.\n    </p>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"bg-sunglow/10 border-2 border-sunglow p-5 md:p-8 rounded-xl my-8\">\n    <h3 class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3\">The Quick Answer</h3>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 text-base md:text-lg mb-4\">\n      If your family has someone handy with electrical work and you want a permanent solution, the <strong>Renogy 400W Premium Kit</strong> is the one—perfect 5-star rating, MPPT controller (way more efficient), and Bluetooth monitoring so you can troubleshoot from Miami. If they just need backup power NOW with zero installation, you're looking at a power station instead (different guide, but the principle stands).\n    </p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FG2VF2V2?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-block px-6 py-3 rounded-full bg-flame text-white font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-flame/90 transition-colors\">\n      See the Renogy 400W Kit →\n    </a>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"mb-12\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-6\">The One to Beat: Complete Kits That Actually Work</h2>\n    \n    <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-xl mb-8 ring-2 ring-lime ring-offset-2 ring-offset-white dark:ring-offset-slate-900\">\n      <span class=\"bg-lime text-raisin px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase mb-4 inline-block\">Editor's Pick</span>\n      <div class=\"flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6\">\n        <div class=\"w-full md:w-64 shrink-0\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/716Cn4QfDsL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"Renogy Premium 400 Watt Solar Kit - Editor's Pick for Cuba\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-xl w-full h-64 object-contain bg-slate-50\" />\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n          <h3 data-asin=\"B0FG2VF2V2\" class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">Renogy Premium 400W 12V Solar Kit</h3>\n          <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold\">5★ (505 reviews)</span>\n          <span class=\"ml-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">$$$$$</span>\n          <p class=\"text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mt-4 mb-3\">\n            <strong class=\"text-flame\">VERDICT: The complete package that justifies the price.</strong>\n          </p>\n          <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-4\">\n            Four 100W panels, 40A MPPT charge controller (not the cheaper PWM type), Bluetooth module for remote monitoring, Z-brackets, adaptor kit, and tray cables. That MPPT controller alone makes this 15-20% more efficient than PWM alternatives—crucial when every watt counts during extended blackouts. The Bluetooth module? Game-changer. Your family can send you screenshots of system performance, and you can troubleshoot without a plane ticket.\n          </p>\n          <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm mb-4\">\n            <strong>Cuba consideration:</strong> 12V system works with standard car batteries available locally. The monocrystalline panels handle heat well—important when rooftops hit 50°C in summer.\n          </p>\n          <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FG2VF2V2?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-block px-6 py-3 rounded-full bg-flame text-white font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-flame/90 transition-colors\">\n            Check Price on Amazon →\n          </a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <blockquote class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl italic text-flame border-l-4 border-flame pl-6 my-10\">\n    \"The MPPT controller alone makes this 15-20% more efficient—crucial when every watt counts during extended blackouts.\"\n  </blockquote>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"mb-12\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4\">Head-to-Head: 400W Kits Compared</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-6\">400 watts is the sweet spot for most Cuban households—enough to run fans, charge phones, power LED lights, and keep a small fridge going during the day.</p>\n    \n    <div class=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8\">\n      \n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg ring-2 ring-lime ring-offset-2 ring-offset-white dark:ring-offset-slate-900\">\n        <span class=\"bg-lime text-raisin px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase mb-3 inline-block\">Best Overall</span>\n        <div class=\"w-full h-44 mb-4\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/716Cn4QfDsL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"Renogy 400W Premium Kit\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-full object-contain bg-slate-50\" />\n        </div>\n        <h3 data-asin=\"B0FG2VF2V2\" class=\"text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">Renogy 400W Premium</h3>\n        <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold\">5★</span>\n        <ul class=\"text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-3 space-y-1\">\n          <li>✓ MPPT controller (40A)</li>\n          <li>✓ Bluetooth monitoring</li>\n          <li>✓ Complete mounting hardware</li>\n          <li>✓ Premium cable set included</li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n      \n      \n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <span class=\"bg-sunglow text-raisin px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase mb-3 inline-block\">Budget Alternative</span>\n        <div class=\"w-full h-44 mb-4\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81NGDGKhAJL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"ECO-WORTHY 400W Kit\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-full object-contain bg-slate-50\" />\n        </div>\n        <h3 data-asin=\"B0BPY72B9R\" class=\"text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">ECO-WORTHY 400W Kit</h3>\n        <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold\">4.3★</span>\n        <ul class=\"text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-3 space-y-1\">\n          <li>✓ MPPT controller (40A)</li>\n          <li>✓ Bluetooth module included</li>\n          <li>✓ Z-brackets included</li>\n          <li>○ Slightly lower review score</li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-700 p-4 rounded-lg\">\n      <strong>The difference?</strong> Both are at the $$$$$ tier, but the Renogy's perfect rating across 500+ reviews suggests better quality control. For something you're shipping 1,500 miles to a place where returns aren't an option, that consistency matters.\n    </p>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"mb-12\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4\">Going Big: 800W+ Systems</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-6\">If your family needs to run a refrigerator full-time or multiple fans across the house, you're looking at 800 watts minimum. Fair warning: these are heavier, more expensive to ship, and require more installation know-how.</p>\n    \n    \n    <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg mb-6 ring-2 ring-sunglow ring-offset-2 ring-offset-white dark:ring-offset-slate-900\">\n      <span class=\"bg-sunglow text-raisin px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase mb-4 inline-block\">Best Value 800W</span>\n      <div class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-5\">\n        <div class=\"w-full sm:w-48 md:w-56 shrink-0\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/713HUQV3X8L._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"18BB 800W Solar Panel Kit\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-56 object-contain bg-slate-50\" />\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n          <h3 data-asin=\"B0FFGTMG46\" class=\"text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">18BB 800W N-Type Panel Kit (4x 200W)</h3>\n          <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold\">4.3★ (435 reviews)</span>\n          <span class=\"ml-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">$$$</span>\n          <p class=\"text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mt-3 mb-2\">\n            <strong class=\"text-flame\">VERDICT: Double the power at mid-range pricing—rare find.</strong>\n          </p>\n          <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm mb-4\">\n            N-Type cells are the newer technology—better efficiency, better heat tolerance, better longevity. At $$$ for 800W, this undercuts the competition significantly. The catch? It's panels only—you'll need to source a charge controller separately. But if your family already has one or you want to choose your own MPPT unit, this is the move.\n          </p>\n          <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FFGTMG46?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-block px-5 py-2 rounded-full bg-flame text-white font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-flame/90 transition-colors text-sm\">\n            Check Price →\n          </a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    \n    <div class=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6\">\n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <div class=\"w-full h-44 mb-4\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81sCnup-X5L._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"Callsun 800W Solar Panel Kit\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-full object-contain bg-slate-50\" />\n        </div>\n        <h3 data-asin=\"B0FZKR417P\" class=\"text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">Callsun 800W Kit (8x 100W)</h3>\n        <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold\">4.6★</span>\n        <span class=\"ml-2 text-slate-500 text-xs\">$$$$$</span>\n        <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm mt-3\">\n          Eight smaller panels instead of four large ones. Easier to ship in multiple boxes, easier to position on irregular rooftops. High-output design and solid 4.6★ rating. Good for complex roof layouts.\n        </p>\n        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FZKR417P?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-block mt-3 px-4 py-2 rounded-full bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-600 text-slate-800 dark:text-white text-sm font-medium no-underline hover:bg-slate-300 dark:hover:bg-slate-500 transition-colors\">\n          View Details →\n        </a>\n      </div>\n      \n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <div class=\"w-full h-44 mb-4\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71pz5YPEjGL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"STAR 870W Solar Panel\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-full object-contain bg-slate-50\" />\n        </div>\n        <h3 data-asin=\"B0DFBSBWDG\" class=\"text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">STAR 870W (2x 435W Panels)</h3>\n        <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold\">4.2★</span>\n        <span class=\"ml-2 text-slate-500 text-xs\">$$$$$</span>\n        <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm mt-3\">\n          Just two massive panels—full-screen design, maintenance-free, 25% efficiency. The 48V/24V flexibility is nice for larger battery banks. Fewer connections mean fewer failure points. Big and heavy though.\n        </p>\n        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DFBSBWDG?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-block mt-3 px-4 py-2 rounded-full bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-600 text-slate-800 dark:text-white text-sm font-medium no-underline hover:bg-slate-300 dark:hover:bg-slate-500 transition-colors\">\n          View Details →\n        </a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"my-10\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4\">How Much Solar Does Your Family Actually Need?</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-6\">Blackouts in Cuba average 8+ hours in many areas. Use this calculator to size the system properly.</p>\n    <solar-sizing>\n  </solar-sizing></section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-8 rounded-2xl mb-10\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4\">The \"No Installation\" Option</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-6\">Not everyone has a family member who can wire a solar system. This one literally plugs into the wall.</p>\n    \n    <div class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-5 bg-white dark:bg-slate-700 p-5 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n      <div class=\"w-full sm:w-48 md:w-56 shrink-0\">\n        <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/51ZNk5gm2ML._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"Plug and Play 800W Solar System\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-56 object-contain bg-slate-50\" />\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n        <h3 data-asin=\"B09D61CP1T\" class=\"text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">Plug and Play 800W Solar System</h3>\n        <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold\">4.5★ (455 reviews)</span>\n        <span class=\"ml-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">$$$$$</span>\n        <p class=\"text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mt-3 mb-2\">\n          <strong class=\"text-flame\">VERDICT: Grid-tie simplicity, but check local regulations.</strong>\n        </p>\n        <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm mb-4\">\n          800W panels plus 800W inverter—plug into any wall outlet and it feeds power back into the house. Revolutionary simple. <strong>But here's the catch:</strong> this is designed